What it is
\i0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs55\fsmilli27648 \cf2 \cb3 The network effect occurs when a large group of people with similar desires clusters on a common platform. Once a critical mass of users has been reached and a unique audience has been established, there is a tipping point, after which the value obtained from the product or service is greater than the price paid.\cb1 \
\
\
\
\cb3 eBay is an excellent example of the network effect in action. After a critical mass of users chose eBay as their primary source of acquiring or selling goods, the service attracted an even greater volume of customers. This market meeting place provides sellers with the best chance of earning the highest sale price possible, while offering buyers the best opportunity to find what they are looking to purchase.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\i\fs71\fsmilli35712 \cf2 \cb3 How it relates to investing
\i0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs55\fsmilli27648 \cf2 \cb3 Network effects can create a sustainable competitive advantage for a company\'97one of the elements we look for in high-quality businesses. For example, one of the reasons Microsoft supported such lofty valuations from its IPO until the bursting of the Internet bubble was that its operating system enjoyed such a massive network effect. Customers had accepted its Windows operating system as the default platform and, up till then, no other company had been able to compete with Microsoft in that space.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

